<Layout title="Now">
    <h1>
        Now
    </h1>
    <p class="lede">
        Last updated: May 2026
    </p>
    <p>
        Welcome to my now page, where you can see what I'm currently up to, both personally and professionally.
    </p>
    <h2>
        Headlines
    </h2>
    <p>
        Last year I bought my first house in with my partner, with whom I had been in a long-distance relationship for 5 years (!!). It's a cosy little place in Stoke-on-Trent, where we have the wild nature of the Peaks almost on our doorstep, and a great local board game cafe (shoutout to Long Rest in Hanley). 
    </p>
    <p>
        In sad news, my time at The Economist came to an end in May 2026 during a round of layoffs. I'm very happy to be keeping in touch with a lot of my former colleagues though, and forcing them to look at pictures of my vegetable trug. My time is currently filled with a lot of gardening, reading, and learning new things in preparation for my next role.
    </p>
    <h2>
        Projects
    </h2>
    <ul>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/emiliawil/emiliawil.dev">emiliawil.dev</a> - This website! Built with Astro and TypeScript.</li>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/emiliawil/dnd-wizard" target="_blank">dnd-wizard</a> - An extremely beginner-friendly D&D character builder built with Next.js and TypeScript.</li>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/emiliawil/solitaire" target="_blank">solitaire</a> - A simple solitaire game built with Next.js and TypeScript. No help from AI, just a fun coding challenge for myself.</li>
        <li>Brushing up on my fundamentals on Codewars, Excersicm, Just Javascript and real-time coding tutorials. My Claude Code hasn't been touched for some time now and I can feel my brain healing!</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
        I'm also taking advantage of my time off to do a lot of reading and engaging in hobbies I haven't had time for in a while, such as gardening, crocheting, painting and creative writing. 
    </p>
